Reasoning: The paper discusses the properties that a modeling language like UML must have to support Extreme Programming, which is a software engineering methodology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses how a diagrammatic programming language must look like to replace a textual programming language, which falls under the sub-category of cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits and problems of using such an approach, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.SD (Software Development), cs.OH (Other Computer Science), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
